The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | After bus, auto turns turtle in New Town
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      After bus, auto turns turtle in New Town
          OUR BUREAU                              
	An autorickshaw overturned near the Jatragachhi crossing on New Town Road on Friday afternoon after being hit by a car heading towards Chinar Park. The auto driver and two passengers inside were injured.        
	Police said the auto had stopped near the crossing to change lanes when the car hit it from behind. I was waiting to take a turn when the car hit my vehicle. I was injured in my forehead and left arm, said Sanjay Mondal, the auto driver.        
	Police said the car might have developed a snag. Both vehicles have been seized. Trader Nabanath Jha, who was driving the car, told the police that he had failed to stop the vehicle because of a snag in the braking system.         
	The injured were taken to Bidhannagar Sub-divisional Hospital.        
	The accident occurred about 50 metres from the place where a Delhi Public School Megacity bus had turned turtle on Thursday, injuring seven.        
	 Fire: Three incidents of fire were reported from across the city on Friday. A short-circuit led to a fire at an electrical goods shop on Ganesh Chandra Avenue around 4.30pm. Five tenders doused the flames.        
	A fire broke out at the APC Road branch of UCO Bank at 1.15pm. Two tenders brought the blaze under control.        
	Around 6.20am, a fire spread from an air-conditioner on the top floor of a four-storeyed building on Ezra Street. Three tenders put out the fire. No injuries have been reported.        
	 Lead-free paints: The state pollution control board on Friday distributed lead-free paints to idol makers in Kalighat. The programme was organised in association with the Potuapara Mritshilpa Unnayan Samity.         
	 Found dead: Sanjay Saha, 35, a BSNL employee and resident of Ichhapur P amp;T quarters in Howrah, was found hanging from the ceiling of his room on Friday morning.        
	 Theft: Gold and silver ornaments weighing 13kg have allegedly been stolen from a temple on Dum Dum Road. The priest detected the theft on Friday morning.        
	 Appointment: V.N. Tripathi, the general manager of Eastern Railway, has taken over as the member staff of the railway board and ex-officio secretary to the Government of India. Tripathi will continue to look after the work of the Eastern Railway general manager for the time being.        
	 Mishap: A 32-year-old trader, Jayanta Dalal, died after a minitruck in which he was travelling overturned early on Friday at Amdanga, on the northern fringes of the city.                                                                                                                                                           
